      "content": "**Key structural elements**\n- **Cationic basic center:** a **protonated amine** (`[NH2+]`) embedded in a **saturated ring** (piperidine-like; actually a constrained cyclic amine). This will be **positively charged at physiological pH**.\n- **Aromatic/hydrophobic domains:**  \n  - One **fluorophenyl** ring (`Fc1ccc(...)cc1`)  \n  - One **fused bicyclic aromatic system** (indole-like: `c2[nH]c3...ccc3c2`), also fluorinated.\n- **H-bonding features:**  \n  - **Indole [nH]** = H-bond donor (not basic)  \n  - **Protonated amine** = strong H-bond donor / ionic interaction center\n- **Overall topology:** a **cationic center tethered to two sizable aromatic systems** via a relatively rigid, bulky scaffold with a defined stereocenter (`[C@H]`).",
