      "content": "hERG blockers commonly show:\n1) **A cationic center** (often a tertiary amine) that can interact electrostatically with residues in the pore region (classically **Phe656/Tyr652 region contributes to binding via \u03c0 interactions; electrostatics help position the ligand**).\n2) **Hydrophobic/aromatic groups** that engage **\u03c0\u2013\u03c0 / hydrophobic contacts** within the channel cavity.\n3) **Appropriate size/shape** to occupy the central cavity and/or access it through fenestrations.",
