    {
      "step_id": "87d2fa36",
      "step_index": 6,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "How this molecule fits:\n- The **permanently/strongly protonated amine** strongly favors **electrostatic attraction** and anchoring in the channel environment.\n- The molecule has **two substantial aromatic surfaces** (fluorophenyl + fused bicyclic heteroaromatic). This increases **lipophilicity and \u03c0-surface area**, both correlated with hERG risk.\n- **Fluorination** can increase **hydrophobicity and metabolic stability**, often increasing exposure and sometimes hERG liability indirectly; it can also strengthen aromatic interactions by tuning electronics (context-dependent).\n- The scaffold is **not overly flexible**, but hERG binding does not require high flexibility; many potent blockers are fairly rigid as long as the **cation\u2013aromatic spatial relationship** matches the binding site geometry.",
